                                    "patching_rect": [ 10.0, 81.0, 528.0, 100.0 ],
                                    "saved_attribute_attributes": {
                                        "textcolor": {
                                            "expression": "themecolor.theme_textcolor"
                                        }
                                    },
                                    "text": "There are different ways to detect onsets depending on what you are interested in. In Data Knot the main ways are via amplitude (dk.onset~), spectral difference (dk.spectralonset~), or novelty (dk.novelty~). Each algorithm is tailored to a different type of material. In general, amplitude-based onset detection is the fastest, but it can only detect changes in amplitude, Spectral onset detection is useful for finding changes in other metrics. Novelty is useful for detecting larger-scale changes in types of material. For more information see the helpfiles for each of the individual objects."
                                }
