                                        "textcolor": {
                                            "expression": "themecolor.theme_textcolor"
                                        }
                                    },
                                    "text": "You can fine tune the onset detection using the macro parameters. The sensitivity parameter adjusts both the on and off thresholds and is the single most important macro parameter to adjust. Raise the sensitivity if you are not getting all your onsets detected, and lower it if too many are being detected. Lockout is the amount of time that has to pass before a new onset can be detected. And floor is is the point below which all signal will be ignored."
                                }
                            },
